name: FLYING THE CLASSIC DASH! Air Canada Express Dash 8-300 Edmonton to Calgary
description:
The Calgary to Edmonton route is easily the most popular regional one within the province of Alberta, and Air Canada Express flies mostly Bombardier Q400s between the two cities.

However, there’s also a flight or two operated by some older de Havilland Canada Dash 8-300s, otherwise known as the “Classic Dash”.

See what I thought of the in-flight experience on this 29-year-old aircraft!
